From a first glance, you’re not going to see much…
-
Stare at this for 1 min..and you'll start to see how much is changing. Just like you used to look at those #Highlight magazines to spot the differences in both #photos. What do you see?! Leave your #comments below.. Look at everything. Height of the #shoulder #blades at the #start vs the #end, #position of the pony tail as #neck and head counter #rotate, and the different levels and angles of #scapula.
-
Lower #back #pain, neck pain, #TMJ, #asthma, and the list goes on with her. We tackled this position after setting her #hips up for a good 30 min prior to allow the change we had hoped for. You can see the top picture, when she is first asked to go into #thoracic #extension with hip extension, you can see the rotation and mid back dysfunction rear it’s ugly head.  From hips and pelvis, to mid back, all the way to the shoulders and neck, nothing wanted to open evenly. That left shoulder was stubborn and not releasing.. after 6 min, the left shoulder releases and she’s able to start extending equally on both sides of the neck, mid back, pelvis, and hips. -
Ending the session with her neck and shoulder tension going away..it was a successful attempt and restoring balance and function to the dysfunction rather than stretch the symptoms 👍🏽😎
-
One movement closer, and one day closer to living pain free.
